cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY 

This paper is about network functions and their programming, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper discusses the need for specifying and checking packet processing operations, which involves ensuring correctness and security, making it relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of contracts, which are a programming language feature, making it relevant to programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for simplifying and checking common dependent packet and header processing logic, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
